<section
  class="relative flex items-center w-full  bg-white"
>
  <div class="relative items-center w-full mx-auto 2xl:max-w-7xl border-b-2 border-black 2xl:border-x-2">
    <div class="relative items-center h-full">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 lg:divide-x-2 divide-black">
        <div class="text-center lg:text-left p-8 lg:p-20 bg-lila-500">
          <div>
            <p
              class="text-3xl lg:text-9xl tracking-tight font-medium text-black      "
            >
              FAQ
            </p>
            <p class="text-xl tracking-wide  mt-4 text-black max-w-xs">
              Answers to commonly asked questions about our platform
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div
          x-data="{
      activeAccordion: '',
      setActiveAccordion(id) {
      this.activeAccordion = (this.activeAccordion == id) ? '' : id
      }
      }"
          class="relative w-full mx-auto lg:col-span-2 text-xl font-medium divide-y-2 divide-black"
        >
          <div
            x-data="{ id: $id('accordion') }"
            :class="{ 'text-black': activeAccordion==id, '  hover:text-lila-900 duration-300': activeAccordion!=id }"
            class="cursor-pointer group text-black       hover:text-lila-900 duration-300"
          >
            <button
              @click="setActiveAccordion(id)"
              class="flex items-center justify-between w-full p-8 text-left select-none"
            >
              <span>How does end-to-end encryption work?</span>
              <div
                class="h-8 w-8 border-2 border-black inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full shadow-tiny shadow-black group-hover:bg-lila-500 group-hover:text-black"
              >
                <svg
                  class="w-5 h-5 duration-300 ease-out text-accent-500"
                  :class="{ '-rotate-[45deg]': activeAccordion==id }"
                  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                  fill="none"
                  viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                  stroke-width="2"
                  stroke="currentColor"
                >
                  <path
                    stroke-linecap="round"
                    stroke-linejoin="round"
                    d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path>
                </svg>
              </div>
            </button>
            <div
              x-show="activeAccordion==id"
              x-collapse=""
              style="display: none;"
            >
              <div
                class="p-8 pt-0 text-slate-600 font-sans text-lg max-w-3xl font-normal"
              >
                End-to-end encryption ensures that only the sender and recipient
                can access the content of a message. The information is
                encrypted on the sender's device and can only be decrypted by
                the intended recipient, preventing any intermediaries, including
                the platform provider, from accessing the data.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div
            x-data="{ id: $id('accordion') }"
            :class="{ 'text-black': activeAccordion==id, '  hover:text-lila-900 duration-300': activeAccordion!=id }"
            class="cursor-pointer group text-black       hover:text-lila-900 duration-300"
          >
            <button
              @click="setActiveAccordion(id)"
              class="flex items-center justify-between w-full p-8 text-left select-none"
            >
              <span
                >Can I access my encrypted data if I forget my encryption key?</span
              >
              <div
                class="h-8 w-8 border-2 border-black inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full shadow-tiny shadow-black group-hover:bg-lila-500 group-hover:text-black"
              >
                <svg
                  class="w-5 h-5 duration-300 ease-out text-accent-500"
                  :class="{ '-rotate-[45deg]': activeAccordion==id }"
                  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                  fill="none"
                  viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                  stroke-width="2"
                  stroke="currentColor"
                >
                  <path
                    stroke-linecap="round"
                    stroke-linejoin="round"
                    d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path>
                </svg>
              </div>
            </button>
            <div
              x-show="activeAccordion==id"
              x-collapse=""
              style="display: none;"
            >
              <div
                class="p-8 pt-0 text-slate-600 font-sans text-lg max-w-3xl font-normal"
              >
                No, forgetting or losing your encryption key means that your
                encrypted data cannot be accessed. This is a crucial security
                measure to ensure that even if someone gains unauthorized access
                to your account, they won't be able to decrypt and view your
                messages or files.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div
            x-data="{ id: $id('accordion') }"
            :class="{ 'text-black': activeAccordion==id, '  hover:text-lila-900 duration-300': activeAccordion!=id }"
            class="cursor-pointer group text-black       hover:text-lila-900 duration-300"
          >
            <button
              @click="setActiveAccordion(id)"
              class="flex items-center justify-between w-full p-8 text-left select-none"
            >
              <span
                >Are there any limitations to the self-destructing messages
                feature?</span
              >
              <div
                class="h-8 w-8 border-2 border-black inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full shadow-tiny shadow-black group-hover:bg-lila-500 group-hover:text-black"
              >
                <svg
                  class="w-5 h-5 duration-300 ease-out text-accent-500"
                  :class="{ '-rotate-[45deg]': activeAccordion==id }"
                  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                  fill="none"
                  viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                  stroke-width="2"
                  stroke="currentColor"
                >
                  <path
                    stroke-linecap="round"
                    stroke-linejoin="round"
                    d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path>
                </svg>
              </div>
            </button>
            <div
              x-show="activeAccordion==id"
              x-collapse=""
              style="display: none;"
            >
              <div
                class="p-8 pt-0 text-slate-600 font-sans text-lg max-w-3xl font-normal"
              >
                Self-destructing messages are designed to automatically delete
                themselves after a specific period or upon being read by the
                recipient. However, it's important to note that the feature only
                removes the message from the devices involved in the
                conversation. Recipients may take screenshots or use other means
                to capture the content, which is beyond the platform's control.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div
            x-data="{ id: $id('accordion') }"
            :class="{ 'text-black': activeAccordion==id, '  hover:text-lila-900 duration-300': activeAccordion!=id }"
            class="cursor-pointer group text-black       hover:text-lila-900 duration-300"
          >
            <button
              @click="setActiveAccordion(id)"
              class="flex items-center justify-between w-full p-8 text-left select-none"
            >
              <span
                >What happens if I enable two-factor authentication and lose my
                device?</span
              >
              <div
                class="h-8 w-8 border-2 border-black inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full shadow-tiny shadow-black group-hover:bg-lila-500 group-hover:text-black"
              >
                <svg
                  class="w-5 h-5 duration-300 ease-out text-accent-500"
                  :class="{ '-rotate-[45deg]': activeAccordion==id }"
                  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                  fill="none"
                  viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                  stroke-width="2"
                  stroke="currentColor"
                >
                  <path
                    stroke-linecap="round"
                    stroke-linejoin="round"
                    d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path>
                </svg>
              </div>
            </button>
            <div
              x-show="activeAccordion==id"
              x-collapse=""
              style="display: none;"
            >
              <div
                class="p-8 pt-0 text-slate-600 font-sans text-lg max-w-3xl font-normal"
              >
                Losing your device doesn't automatically compromise your
                account's security. It's recommended to contact our support team
                as soon as possible to disable the two-factor authentication on
                your lost device and set up the authentication on your new
                device. This process will help protect your account from
                unauthorized access while ensuring you can regain access to it.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div
            x-data="{ id: $id('accordion') }"
            :class="{ 'text-black': activeAccordion==id, '  hover:text-lila-900 duration-300': activeAccordion!=id }"
            class="cursor-pointer group text-black       hover:text-lila-900 duration-300"
          >
            <button
              @click="setActiveAccordion(id)"
              class="flex items-center justify-between w-full p-8 text-left select-none"
            >
              <span
                >Is my personal information shared or sold to third parties?</span
              >
              <div
                class="h-8 w-8 border-2 border-black inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full shadow-tiny shadow-black group-hover:bg-lila-500 group-hover:text-black"
              >
                <svg
                  class="w-5 h-5 duration-300 ease-out text-accent-500"
                  :class="{ '-rotate-[45deg]': activeAccordion==id }"
                  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                  fill="none"
                  viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                  stroke-width="2"
                  stroke="currentColor"
                >
                  <path
                    stroke-linecap="round"
                    stroke-linejoin="round"
                    d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path>
                </svg>
              </div>
            </button>
            <div
              x-show="activeAccordion==id"
              x-collapse=""
              style="display: none;"
            >
              <div
                class="p-8 pt-0 text-slate-600 font-sans text-lg max-w-3xl font-normal"
              >
                No, we strictly adhere to a privacy-centric approach. Your
                personal information is never shared, sold, or monetized. We
                prioritize your privacy and ensure that your data remains
                confidential and only accessible to you.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div
            x-data="{ id: $id('accordion') }"
            :class="{ 'text-black': activeAccordion==id, '  hover:text-lila-900 duration-300': activeAccordion!=id }"
            class="cursor-pointer group text-black       hover:text-lila-900 duration-300"
          >
            <button
              @click="setActiveAccordion(id)"
              class="flex items-center justify-between w-full p-8 text-left select-none"
            >
              <span>Can I use this platform on multiple devices?</span>
              <div
                class="h-8 w-8 border-2 border-black inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full shadow-tiny shadow-black group-hover:bg-lila-500 group-hover:text-black"
              >
                <svg
                  class="w-5 h-5 duration-300 ease-out text-accent-500"
                  :class="{ '-rotate-[45deg]': activeAccordion==id }"
                  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                  fill="none"
                  viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                  stroke-width="2"
                  stroke="currentColor"
                >
                  <path
                    stroke-linecap="round"
                    stroke-linejoin="round"
                    d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path>
                </svg>
              </div>
            </button>
            <div
              x-show="activeAccordion==id"
              x-collapse=""
              style="display: none;"
            >
              <div
                class="p-8 pt-0 text-slate-600 font-sans text-lg max-w-3xl font-normal"
              >
                Yes, you can access our platform on multiple devices. Your
                encrypted data remains synced across all devices, allowing you
                to seamlessly communicate and access your files and messages
                from anywhere.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div
            x-data="{ id: $id('accordion') }"
            :class="{ 'text-black': activeAccordion==id, '  hover:text-lila-900 duration-300': activeAccordion!=id }"
            class="cursor-pointer group text-black       hover:text-lila-900 duration-300"
          >
            <button
              @click="setActiveAccordion(id)"
              class="flex items-center justify-between w-full p-8 text-left select-none"
            >
              <span
                >Are there any storage limitations for files and documents?</span
              >
              <div
                class="h-8 w-8 border-2 border-black inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full shadow-tiny shadow-black group-hover:bg-lila-500 group-hover:text-black"
              >
                <svg
                  class="w-5 h-5 duration-300 ease-out text-accent-500"
                  :class="{ '-rotate-[45deg]': activeAccordion==id }"
                  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                  fill="none"
                  viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                  stroke-width="2"
                  stroke="currentColor"
                >
                  <path
                    stroke-linecap="round"
                    stroke-linejoin="round"
                    d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path>
                </svg>
              </div>
            </button>
            <div
              x-show="activeAccordion==id"
              x-collapse=""
              style="display: none;"
            >
              <div
                class="p-8 pt-0 text-slate-600 font-sans text-lg max-w-3xl font-normal"
              >
                Our platform provides ample storage space for your files and
                documents. However, there may be storage limitations based on
                the pricing plan you choose. We offer flexible plans to suit
                your needs and provide options to upgrade if you require
                additional storage capacity.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div
            x-data="{ id: $id('accordion') }"
            :class="{ 'text-black': activeAccordion==id, '  hover:text-lila-900 duration-300': activeAccordion!=id }"
            class="cursor-pointer group text-black       hover:text-lila-900 duration-300"
          >
            <button
              @click="setActiveAccordion(id)"
              class="flex items-center justify-between w-full p-8 text-left select-none"
            >
              <span>Is it possible to export my data from the platform?</span>
              <div
                class="h-8 w-8 border-2 border-black inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full shadow-tiny shadow-black group-hover:bg-lila-500 group-hover:text-black"
              >
                <svg
                  class="w-5 h-5 duration-300 ease-out text-accent-500"
                  :class="{ '-rotate-[45deg]': activeAccordion==id }"
                  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                  fill="none"
                  viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                  stroke-width="2"
                  stroke="currentColor"
                >
                  <path
                    stroke-linecap="round"
                    stroke-linejoin="round"
                    d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path>
                </svg>
              </div>
            </button>
            <div
              x-show="activeAccordion==id"
              x-collapse=""
              style="display: none;"
            >
              <div
                class="p-8 pt-0 text-slate-600 font-sans text-lg max-w-3xl font-normal"
              >
                Yes, you can export your data from the platform. We offer export
                features that allow you to download your messages, files, and
                documents, ensuring you have a local copy for backup or
                migration purposes. It provides you with greater control and
                flexibility over your data.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
